FBIS4-35199 "drnes104dd_94017" FBIS-NES-94-104 Daily Report 30 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs Al-Tibi Comments on `Serious' Financial Situation Al-Tibi Comments on `Serious' Financial Situation JN3005212794 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 30 May 94 JN3005212794 Sanaa Voice of Palestine Arabic BFN [Text] Brother Ahmad al-Tibi, adviser to brother President Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], has said that the financial crisis in the self-rule area is serious and that if donor countries do not begin paying what they had promised to pay, the Palestinian institutions in the Gaza Strip and Jericho will collapse very soon, probably within days.
